  <div class="right">
    <div class="content">
      <div
        class="annotation"
        id="dem-poll-1"
        data-annotation-id="1"
        role="comment"
      >
        <p>
          The scale on this first bar chart is <i>hilarious</i>, particularly
          juxtaposed above the chart just below it (which captures the full 100%
          of respondents, while the same amount of space fits maybe 30% of
          respondents for this question).
        </p>
        <p>
          I can help them out a little bit by editing in the bar for the
          remainder of the &ldquo;non-Harris voters&rdquo; who don&rsquo;t hold
          crypto:
        </p>
        <div class="in-text-image wide bordered">
          <a
            href="https://storage.mollywhite.net/micro/dem_polling_image_1-2.png"
          >
            <img
              src="https://storage.mollywhite.net/micro/dem_polling_image_1-2.png"
              alt="Same as previous, but an orange bar with the proper width to
            represent the remaining 82% of respondents has been edited in. This
